            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-04T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-04T04:00:00-05:00" n="1172" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0090/5–449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-04T17:00:00+08:00">May 4, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 5—12:30 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>763. Re Contel 734 [<hi rend="italic">735</hi>], April 30. Sent today double
                    registry letter May 3 addressed Peiping mayor enclosing copy communications sent
                    previously headquarters PLA.<note n="50" xml:id="d1172fn50">People’s Liberation
                        Army.</note> This course followed because general unreceptivity Aliens
                    Affairs Office re subject in point.</p>
                <p>Passed Nanking 483, OffEmb Canton 96, Shanghai 511.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
